WEBVTT

00:00.354 --> 00:02.718
I get to speak all over the country, the world.

00:02.798 --> 00:06.343
You know, I've spoken at some of the biggest churches in the country.

00:07.505 --> 00:11.551
Certainly some of the biggest companies in the world.

00:12.733 --> 00:15.557
But I always feel that this is my home.

00:19.042 --> 00:21.486
And because, you know, I always feel welcome here.

00:21.686 --> 00:25.572
You know, your pastor is, I don't have to tell you, he's your pastor.

00:26.614 --> 00:29.458
But he's such a great guy.

00:29.986 --> 00:38.275
Him and His wife always inspires me, just His humbleness and what He's built.

00:39.236 --> 00:40.697
You know that God isn't His life.

00:42.019 --> 00:44.501
How do you know that God isn't His life?

00:44.521 --> 00:47.044
Just look at His life and you can see God all over Him.

00:48.846 --> 00:50.307
And that's why I enjoy coming here.

00:50.367 --> 00:51.629
You know, I'm going to talk to you.

00:52.049 --> 00:56.594
I haven't shared in a while my testimony.

00:57.122 --> 01:00.286
on how Cheetos came into existence, how I got saved.

01:00.306 --> 01:03.850
So I'm going to quickly try to do that.

01:03.930 --> 01:07.574
I did that years ago, but I'm sure some of you have never heard that story.

01:08.816 --> 01:15.724
I know I got 30 minutes, but I'll tell you what, I'll tell you when to start the clock, okay?

01:15.744 --> 01:21.230
But I also want to talk to you about creating a revolution in your life.

01:22.752 --> 01:24.274
Now, what is a revolution?

01:25.698 --> 01:31.004
A revolution is something that was always there, but it's been revealed or unveiled to you.

01:31.024 --> 01:31.945
It was always there.

01:32.145 --> 01:34.948
I'm gonna give you a revelation right now.

01:37.951 --> 01:39.753
These glasses were always in my pocket.

01:40.494 --> 01:41.595
They were always there.

01:42.336 --> 01:43.677
I just revealed it to you.

01:44.959 --> 01:49.463
So you can take one revelation to create a revolution in your life.

01:50.585 --> 01:51.826
And what is a revolution?

01:52.514 --> 01:55.819
A revolution is something that just changes your life completely.

01:55.859 --> 02:01.367
And that's what happened in my life when I first got saved.

02:02.269 --> 02:09.980
You know, I like to tell people, you know, that I stopped going to school in the sixth grade.

02:10.000 --> 02:13.365
When I got saved, I couldn't read, I couldn't write.

02:13.906 --> 02:19.515
You know, the Bible's a difficult book to read, but something happened in my life.

02:20.196 --> 02:21.778
God awoke in certain things.

02:22.850 --> 02:23.831
I never knew.

02:23.871 --> 02:26.794
Listen to me, I'm going to be honest with you, okay?

02:27.575 --> 02:28.456
I'm not making anything.

02:28.877 --> 02:31.720
I never knew until I got saved that I was brilliant.

02:34.262 --> 02:37.946
I'm probably the most uneducated, brilliant person you will ever meet.

02:39.788 --> 02:48.818
Because their brilliance was a revelation that was always there, but then it was revealed to me.

02:52.194 --> 03:00.725
And I know I love that scripture when Hosea wrote in chapter four, I believe it is, my people are destroyed for lack of.

03:02.046 --> 03:02.407
Okay.

03:03.789 --> 03:06.292
Did he say my people are destroyed because of the devil?

03:07.994 --> 03:08.835
Because of drugs?

03:09.856 --> 03:11.799
He said, because lack of knowledge.

03:13.140 --> 03:17.746
You know that the knowledge of God can separate you from the knowledge of man.

03:19.266 --> 03:23.533
Once you get a hold of the knowledge of God in your life, there is no competition for you.

03:23.793 --> 03:24.975
You are separated.

03:25.015 --> 03:31.405
How does somebody that never went to high school teach at Harvard?

03:32.367 --> 03:36.894
Notre Dame, Purdue, Pepperdine, USC, you can't explain it.

03:39.778 --> 03:43.825
How do you explain to somebody that can barely read, had written two bestsellers?

03:45.728 --> 03:47.250
Thank God for spell check, huh?

03:50.050 --> 03:52.273
And I know people have told me, you know, you're gonna write a book.

03:52.554 --> 03:56.900
Sometimes, brothers and sisters, when God gives you an idea of revelation, don't tell anybody.

03:58.422 --> 03:59.143
Don't tell anybody.

03:59.624 --> 04:01.287
I'm gonna share with you in my story.

04:01.307 --> 04:08.838
So, if we can, let's just check out one scripture.

04:14.386 --> 04:15.307
May one minute here.

04:17.270 --> 04:19.954
This is kind of the scripture that started it for me in my life.

04:21.794 --> 04:23.937
You know, there's three things that I want to do today, okay?

04:24.978 --> 04:29.023
I want to inspire you, I want to encourage you, I don't want to remind you.

04:30.304 --> 04:39.175
Now, I'm a student of, I study Hebrew, I study Latin, I study French, I study the Greek, and somebody said, you should study English.

04:42.319 --> 04:43.060
If I'm dead, I will.

04:46.865 --> 04:47.826
Three things I want to do.

04:48.802 --> 04:55.612
So the word inspire, many of our words today, I love that come from the Greek philosophers as one of the greatest minds of all time.

04:57.194 --> 05:00.559
The word philosophy, sometimes in the Christian church, it gets a bad rap.

05:01.220 --> 05:02.102
Oh, he's a philosopher.

05:02.122 --> 05:04.125
Well, you know the word philosopher comes from two places.

05:04.685 --> 05:06.448
It means somebody who loves to think.

05:06.688 --> 05:08.831
That's what a philosopher is, somebody who loves to think.

05:09.853 --> 05:13.739
And another word that gets a bad rap in the church is science.

05:15.742 --> 05:18.706
You know, to study science is to study the mind of God.

05:20.226 --> 05:23.130
Albert Einstein, one of the greatest minds of all time, he said this.

05:23.591 --> 05:27.978
He said that if a scientist doesn't believe in God, it's because they haven't studied science long enough.

05:31.443 --> 05:32.765
I love to study science.

05:34.407 --> 05:37.852
It gives me the revelations of the secrets of how God did it.

05:39.294 --> 05:44.422
When you see a scientist explaining something, they're just telling, trying to figure out how did God do it.

05:45.924 --> 05:47.627
So the word inspire comes from the Greeks.

05:47.647 --> 05:49.810
It simply means to breathe life into someone.

05:50.434 --> 05:51.596
That's what I want to do this morning.

05:51.616 --> 05:53.358
I just want to breathe life into you for a moment.

05:53.378 --> 05:54.459
It's just for a moment.

05:55.240 --> 05:57.784
Second thing I want to do is I want to encourage you.

05:57.804 --> 05:59.025
What does it mean to encourage someone?

05:59.045 --> 06:03.731
It means to grab courage and put it in their deepest being that they stand up and they're never the same again.

06:03.752 --> 06:05.674
I want to encourage you.

06:08.097 --> 06:12.803
Young people, stay away from people who discourage you.

06:12.823 --> 06:17.810
To discourage someone who means to go into their deepest being and pull out their courage that they never the same again.

06:19.074 --> 06:24.321
The last thing that I'd like to do is I'd like to remind you, and you're thinking, remind me of what?

06:24.381 --> 06:25.803
Remind you of who you are.

06:25.823 --> 06:35.576
Remind you of the value that you are to humanity, the value that you are to this church, to your family, to your job, to your career.

06:36.497 --> 06:38.519
Your value isn't tied into your bank account.

06:40.742 --> 06:45.449
My bank account was zero, so you were telling me that when I first started, I had zero value?

06:46.109 --> 06:46.610
That's what?

06:47.170 --> 06:51.957
Man may tell you that, but God saw you as something that is so valuable that you cannot be replaced.

06:52.738 --> 06:54.741
There isn't two of you brothers and sisters.

06:56.003 --> 06:57.045
There's only one of you.

06:58.046 --> 07:00.530
If there was two of you, one of you wouldn't be needed.

07:00.550 --> 07:04.796
So let me just start off real quick.

07:05.377 --> 07:08.141
In Proverbs chapter 18 verse 16.

07:09.022 --> 07:12.648
And this is a scripture that my, are we gonna put it up?

07:12.908 --> 07:14.130
Proverbs 18, 16.

07:16.898 --> 07:17.459
No?

07:17.479 --> 07:19.502
Yes?

07:19.522 --> 07:19.862
Where is it?

07:19.882 --> 07:20.182
Where is it?

07:20.603 --> 07:21.324
Okay, there we go.

07:21.404 --> 07:23.627
Okay, well, I'm not gonna read it, you can see it.

07:24.789 --> 07:25.910
That saved me some time.

07:26.972 --> 07:30.516
But you know that that's the scripture when we first got saved, me and my wife Judy.

07:30.857 --> 07:32.900
Now let me tell you something about my wife Judy, okay?

07:32.920 --> 07:36.044
We've been married, oh, about 47, 48 years.

07:36.565 --> 07:38.167
We've been together since we were kids.

07:39.569 --> 07:39.889
Thank you.

07:42.192 --> 07:46.578
And I remember, it was about four years ago,

07:46.722 --> 07:58.620
At Harvard, I had told everybody, oh, yeah, I've been married for 47 years, and the whole auditorium was like, chief, I'm barely 20 years old.

08:00.142 --> 08:06.031
So the question came up, Mr. Monson is, you've been married twice as long as I've been alive.

08:06.071 --> 08:09.416
Do you and your wife ever argue?

08:11.358 --> 08:13.442
And I said, do me and Judy ever argue?

08:15.164 --> 08:16.466
Brothers and sisters, this is the truth.

08:17.378 --> 08:18.900
This is how I answered.

08:18.920 --> 08:20.321
Judy told me this a long time ago.

08:20.501 --> 08:24.506
She said this, Richard, I was with you when you had nothing.

08:24.526 --> 08:25.827
I ain't leaving now.

08:28.030 --> 08:30.032
So I will be married until the day I die.

08:33.075 --> 08:34.497
So we both grew up together.

08:34.537 --> 08:35.638
We're from the hood.

08:36.819 --> 08:42.866
A lot of my leadership sometimes doesn't make sense to well educated people because I'm from the hood.

08:43.138 --> 08:47.884
Just because you have a degree from Harvard does no way make you any smarter than I am.

08:48.324 --> 08:50.246
I have a degree that comes from heaven.

08:50.286 --> 09:01.380
The knowledge of God separates you from the, there is no competition when you are filled with the knowledge of God.

09:03.923 --> 09:05.805
So this is the scripture that my wife gave me.

09:07.627 --> 09:10.290
Now, I'm from the hood.

09:11.490 --> 09:15.216
Violence being a part of my life till I got saved.

09:15.576 --> 09:16.778
I grew up dodging bullets.

09:17.680 --> 09:18.801
My father's been shot.

09:19.222 --> 09:20.163
My mom's been shot at.

09:20.203 --> 09:21.305
My brother's been shot at.

09:21.325 --> 09:24.991
10 brothers and sisters, every one of us have been injured.

09:25.011 --> 09:26.673
I used to bail my mom out of jail.

09:27.655 --> 09:28.416
That's how it was.

09:29.918 --> 09:31.481
And today people tell me, you know what Richard?

09:32.222 --> 09:33.143
You're still ghetto.

09:35.527 --> 09:36.228
I'll accept it.

09:36.549 --> 09:38.492
Matter of fact, let me show you how ghetto I am.

09:38.532 --> 09:40.114
This suit,

09:42.722 --> 09:53.998
This Thai Versace, this shirt Valentino, this shoes Gucci, this belt Walmart.

09:56.721 --> 09:57.462
Is that ghetto?

09:59.305 --> 10:02.209
See, but that's part of our DNA.

10:03.331 --> 10:08.518
You see, people who have that type of a background, people like you and I, we are visionaries.

10:09.119 --> 10:11.602
We can see things that other people can't see.

10:12.450 --> 10:13.731
It separates us.

10:15.173 --> 10:17.235
We can go to places that other people can't go.

10:17.275 --> 10:20.839
We can dress half stylish and they still wear Walmart.

10:22.060 --> 10:23.001
Because that's who we are.

10:23.041 --> 10:24.183
Other people can't do that.

10:24.203 --> 10:25.144
That is a blessing.

10:25.164 --> 10:28.547
Once you recognize that where you came from, it's a blessing.

10:30.509 --> 10:34.233
Brothers and sisters, there is nothing wrong with your past.

10:34.353 --> 10:35.174
Good or bad.

10:35.795 --> 10:39.419
Your past is a pillar to help sustain your future.

10:39.739 --> 10:42.322
You will recognize that someday if you haven't already.

10:44.578 --> 10:48.144
So my wife said, Richard, God's going to use your gift.

10:48.164 --> 10:49.666
And you're going to stand before the kings.

10:50.888 --> 10:52.290
And I'm like, what are you talking about, Judy?

10:52.310 --> 10:53.432
I don't have no education.

10:53.472 --> 10:54.353
I don't have no gift.

10:55.435 --> 10:56.156
I'm a janitor.

10:58.339 --> 10:59.401
I finally got ahold of it.

11:01.104 --> 11:11.139
This is my gift was to mob floors so that, you know, when I started working, I didn't have very much money.

11:12.161 --> 11:13.042
I was making, you know,

11:13.666 --> 11:15.749
100 bucks a week.

11:15.769 --> 11:20.916
And I would mop that floor and I would say this, God, I'm gonna mop this floor for you.

11:22.078 --> 11:23.580
Receive this as an offering.

11:24.782 --> 11:28.748
I'm gonna take everybody's trash shop for you.

11:28.968 --> 11:30.310
Receive this as an offering.

11:31.171 --> 11:33.014
Little did I know what I was saying.

11:34.256 --> 11:35.978
Be faithful on the little things.

11:35.998 --> 11:37.260
He'll make a ruler over.

11:39.243 --> 11:41.426
At one time I had 50,000 employees.

11:42.562 --> 11:45.325
And it started because I was mopping floors.

11:46.767 --> 11:51.032
It started my wealth building, started when that bucket came around.

11:53.495 --> 11:54.676
And I dropped in seed.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.180
Let me give you some godly knowledge.

12:00.163 --> 12:02.505
The seed, any type of seed.

12:03.707 --> 12:06.290
The seed holds the blueprints.

12:06.330 --> 12:06.830
Listen to me.

12:08.012 --> 12:09.874
The seed holds the blueprints.

12:12.162 --> 12:14.666
for the type of fruit it's going to grow.

12:15.627 --> 12:27.704
So when you plant the seed of the soil, the seed sends a signal to the soil and it tells the soil, these are all the nutrients I need to grow this orange.

12:28.986 --> 12:37.618
So when you drop that seed for a new house, that seed sends a signal in the spirit, these are all the nutrients I need to get this house for them.

12:42.562 --> 12:47.829
One day, me and my wife looked at my bank, our bank account, and said, man, this is... What the heck happened here?

12:49.310 --> 12:49.611
You know?

12:50.672 --> 12:53.716
We have more money than, you know, we never dreamed of.

12:54.417 --> 12:55.638
So we started a foundation.

12:55.678 --> 12:58.682
We started sending kids from the hood to college.

12:59.723 --> 13:00.564
We started feeding.

13:00.624 --> 13:03.408
We fed over a million people across the world.

13:06.892 --> 13:11.698
Every year, we buy 50,000 pairs of brand new shoes, brand new shoes.

13:11.906 --> 13:14.289
that we give them to kids that can't afford them.

13:14.729 --> 13:16.251
And somebody says, why do you do that?

13:16.732 --> 13:17.873
Because I can.

13:17.933 --> 13:23.860
What I do should not be unique.

13:23.880 --> 13:25.142
Each one of you should have that.

13:25.202 --> 13:26.764
Each one of you should have a foundation.

13:29.747 --> 13:30.548
Build the foundation.

13:30.568 --> 13:31.409
Let God fill it up.

13:32.150 --> 13:34.733
And I guarantee you that one day you're going to look at your bank account.

13:34.753 --> 13:35.454
Oh my God.

13:36.335 --> 13:39.058
Because you see, you are actually an ATM for God.

13:40.706 --> 13:43.450
It's not your job to fill up the ATM, it's his job.

13:46.354 --> 13:48.037
So Judy said you're gonna stand before.

13:48.057 --> 13:51.963
I had no idea how that, but that came to pass.

13:53.104 --> 13:57.671
I have had lunch or dinner with every US president since Ronald Reagan.

13:57.711 --> 13:59.975
I've spoken at the White House numerous times.

14:00.896 --> 14:03.560
2005, I spoke at the United Nations.

14:04.101 --> 14:06.424
You can't get an invitation to the United Nations.

14:07.846 --> 14:10.290
And I remember walking up the stairs

14:10.882 --> 14:15.547
And, you know, it must have been, I don't know, a thousand ambassadors there.

14:15.567 --> 14:27.719
I remember walking up the stairs, and you know that God has a way of stopping time and just speaking to you, yet time is still moving around you, but you and him are having a conversation.

14:28.900 --> 14:34.265
And I remember walking up and God said, remember when you cried out?

14:35.867 --> 14:39.090
Because when I first got saved, my mind was fried from drugs.

14:40.034 --> 14:40.855
No school.

14:41.536 --> 14:42.197
And I cried.

14:42.237 --> 14:44.640
I said, God, please don't leave me here.

14:46.363 --> 14:48.065
I have nothing to offer anybody.

14:49.507 --> 14:52.731
Your word says that if any man lack wisdom, let him ask of God.

14:52.791 --> 14:54.634
Your word says, put on the mind of Christ.

14:54.694 --> 14:55.655
I've done these things.

14:57.277 --> 14:59.160
And God said, look at what I've done with you, Richard.

15:00.902 --> 15:02.484
The world comes to hear you speak.

15:04.808 --> 15:07.932
All because of that scripture that Judy gave me.

15:07.952 --> 15:09.554
Your gift is going to lead you to stand.

15:10.626 --> 15:12.529
before Kings.

15:14.632 --> 15:33.441
Now you know that I grew up during a civil rights movement, but I wasn't old enough to have an impact on the movement, but I was old enough that the movement had an impact on my life, because here what happened, desegregation comes into existence, and I grew up in a labor camp.

15:34.683 --> 15:37.908
We lived in one room, no kitchen, no bathroom, everything was outside.

15:38.609 --> 15:39.570
We lived in one room,

15:39.842 --> 15:41.103
Everybody there picked grapes.

15:41.984 --> 15:47.069
Have the residents were Italians and the other half were Latinos.

15:47.089 --> 15:57.058
And so desegregation comes into existence and they pick my school to take eight kids to integrate them out of school across town.

15:58.219 --> 15:58.760
Ten kids.

15:59.600 --> 16:01.502
I'm the second oldest, I'm the oldest male.

16:02.343 --> 16:05.546
And mama's getting her oldest son ready for school.

16:06.507 --> 16:09.810
Let me take you on a trip in the sixties, okay, so relax.

16:11.362 --> 16:14.005
So mama's getting her all this sun ready for school, which is me.

16:15.487 --> 16:16.188
And I'm crying.

16:17.830 --> 16:20.453
And mama says, chion, porque yoras.

16:21.634 --> 16:22.956
Cry, baby, why are you crying?

16:24.537 --> 16:26.259
Porque no quiero y de esta squela.

16:26.980 --> 16:28.382
Cuz I don't want to go to that school.

16:29.663 --> 16:30.665
Porque no miho.

16:31.145 --> 16:31.946
Why not, son?

16:32.967 --> 16:35.210
Porque todos avlan ingles.

16:35.230 --> 16:36.692
Because everybody speaks English.

16:38.193 --> 16:38.674
Mom.

16:39.042 --> 16:42.567
How can you send me to a school where I can barely speak English?

16:43.828 --> 16:46.211
People tell me, Rick, you can still barely speak English.

16:48.354 --> 16:49.856
And Mama said, well, it's the law.

16:51.238 --> 16:51.979
I didn't understand.

16:52.039 --> 16:53.121
It's OK. We went.

16:54.302 --> 16:55.624
And my uncle took us.

16:55.704 --> 16:56.785
And there's eight of us there.

16:56.826 --> 16:58.067
And here comes the yellow bus.

17:00.150 --> 17:01.191
There goes the yellow bus.

17:02.613 --> 17:03.394
It never stopped.

17:04.175 --> 17:06.258
You should have seen eight happy Mexican kids.

17:08.418 --> 17:09.419
Wondering what had happened.

17:09.439 --> 17:11.422
I told my uncle, it's a Mexican holiday.

17:11.442 --> 17:12.363
We don't have to go to school.

17:14.445 --> 17:18.170
Then all of a sudden I heard a, like a bath fire.

17:18.250 --> 17:20.453
And we looked, and here comes this green bus.

17:21.914 --> 17:24.097
The ugly bus, you can imagine.

17:25.178 --> 17:27.141
That's the bus that they sent to pick us up.

17:28.042 --> 17:32.087
I looked at that bus and I'm like, I don't want to ride that ugly thing.

17:32.187 --> 17:36.052
I want to get on the yellow bus with Bobby and Johnny and Mary and Susie.

17:36.392 --> 17:38.034
I want to be like those kids.

17:38.754 --> 17:49.469
Why do I have to, it wasn't until I was older that I realized that many times you have to revisit your path so that you can find your future.

17:49.869 --> 17:51.992
As I said, nothing wrong with your path, good or bad.

17:53.274 --> 17:54.155
It dawned on me.

17:55.357 --> 18:02.326
It was the time in the society of that day that said, let's get these kids right here.

18:02.987 --> 18:08.274
Put them on this ugly green bus, parade them across town so everybody can see the, guess what?

18:08.674 --> 18:11.639
They're not good enough to be like those kids.

18:12.400 --> 18:14.143
Well, as a child, you take that on.

18:15.105 --> 18:18.691
You're not good enough to be like all the other kids.

18:21.315 --> 18:22.036
One more scripture.

18:24.480 --> 18:26.063
Exodus chapter four, verse two.

18:29.328 --> 18:35.378
I love when Moses is having a conversation with God.

18:36.770 --> 18:39.494
You know, and I love to study Moses because I look at him.

18:39.514 --> 18:54.116
Moses was, I mean, he was, he was from the camp of the enemy and God raised him up in that situation knowing he was going to use him over here.

18:55.357 --> 18:59.484
I realize now that everything I went through was for a purpose and a reason.

19:00.545 --> 19:03.890
Some things that your children will go through, hang in there.

19:04.290 --> 19:06.173
It's for a purpose and a reason.

19:06.213 --> 19:08.036
They're being built up like Moses.

19:08.797 --> 19:12.543
First of all, God was gonna give Moses the chain commandments.

19:13.685 --> 19:21.817
Now at the time, only about 3% of Israel could read and write.

19:23.079 --> 19:25.363
So God needed somebody who could read and write.

19:25.383 --> 19:30.691
So of course he got somebody who was one of the most educated individuals at the time was Moses.

19:31.452 --> 19:32.754
So he could handle the writing.

19:33.122 --> 19:35.305
Little details that God never misses.

19:36.587 --> 19:41.414
And then I know when God said, when Moses said, well, who are you?

19:42.315 --> 19:42.996
What is your name?

19:44.258 --> 19:47.643
And God said, I am who I am.

19:49.185 --> 19:50.407
You know what he was telling Moses?

19:51.589 --> 19:53.812
I am whoever you need me to be.

19:53.832 --> 19:57.938
If you are sick, I am the one that heals you.

19:59.170 --> 20:00.512
Are you a poverty?

20:00.712 --> 20:02.113
I am the one that blesses you.

20:02.374 --> 20:04.476
I am everything that you need.

20:04.516 --> 20:14.468
Then he said, well, how am I going to do?

20:14.488 --> 20:15.329
I don't have anything.

20:17.011 --> 20:17.872
My favorite part.

20:18.733 --> 20:20.135
This is what I want you to understand.

20:20.175 --> 20:25.121
Everything that you have to be successful is right in front of you.

20:25.181 --> 20:25.641
It's in you.

20:25.661 --> 20:26.322
It's in your hand.

20:28.066 --> 20:29.648
And God told Moses, what do you have in your hand?

20:29.688 --> 20:30.349
He's a stick.

20:32.112 --> 20:32.993
That's what God uses.

20:33.093 --> 20:34.054
What do you have in your hand?

20:34.135 --> 20:34.615
A stick.

20:35.737 --> 20:36.318
Throw it down.

20:37.099 --> 20:38.140
Turn it into a snake.

20:38.941 --> 20:39.742
God said, pick it up.

20:39.783 --> 20:40.884
Moses, I'm not gonna pick it up.

20:40.924 --> 20:42.006
You know why I said I don't wanna pick it up?

20:42.026 --> 20:42.847
Because it's gonna bite me.

20:43.628 --> 20:44.469
What did he mean by that?

20:46.772 --> 20:50.117
Moses felt that all the bad things that he had done were gonna come back to bite him.

20:50.137 --> 20:51.118
And God said, no, pick it up.

20:52.180 --> 20:53.762
Your pastor's gonna come back to bite you.

20:54.003 --> 20:54.884
You need to understand that.

20:54.904 --> 20:56.466
Your pastor's never gonna come back to bite you.

20:56.898 --> 20:57.619
So here we are.

20:57.779 --> 21:00.563
We get off at the school, right off the bus.

21:01.965 --> 21:05.550
We go to class, trying to figure out what the teacher's saying.

21:05.650 --> 21:08.694
It's not too bad, but then there's one sound that's international.

21:08.734 --> 21:09.935
Every child knows this sound.

21:11.778 --> 21:12.579
You want that sound in?

21:12.619 --> 21:15.883
It's out of the recess bell.

21:17.686 --> 21:19.128
I didn't need an interpretation.

21:19.468 --> 21:20.369
I knew what that meant.

21:21.751 --> 21:22.312
Lunch time.

21:23.974 --> 21:26.738
What a relief.

21:27.938 --> 21:33.546
Me and my friends, eight of us, seven of us, total eight, sat together.

21:37.131 --> 21:43.740
Remember I said that something in your hand that God is gonna use, create a revolution in your life.

21:45.102 --> 21:47.005
But you gotta see it as a revelation first.

21:48.988 --> 21:52.713
So I remember I pulled out my lunch, ready to take a bite.

21:54.756 --> 21:56.338
Everybody's staring at me,

21:56.802 --> 21:58.324
Why do you think everybody was staring at me?

22:00.587 --> 22:01.948
Because there was a burrito.

22:03.610 --> 22:08.116
You got to remember, it was 1960 something, the world hadn't seen a burrito yet.

22:10.058 --> 22:13.943
Contrary to popular belief, Taco Bell didn't introduce the burrito to the world.

22:14.203 --> 22:15.144
Me and my mom did.

22:17.727 --> 22:21.351
But the truth was, I was embarrassed.

22:21.371 --> 22:23.474
I was embarrassed because my English sucked.

22:24.514 --> 22:27.379
I was embarrassed for being on that green bus.

22:27.399 --> 22:30.986
I was embarrassed because everybody was staring at my lunch.

22:31.006 --> 22:37.257
So I remember I went home and I told my mom, mama, get a home baloney sandwich, kaloon cupcake.

22:38.419 --> 22:42.647
Mama, I want a baloney sandwich and a cupcake, like the other kids.

22:43.589 --> 22:45.171
Because I want to be like them, mama.

22:46.834 --> 22:47.816
I don't want to be different.

22:47.836 --> 22:48.818
I want to be like them.

22:49.218 --> 22:54.746
But mama being the marketing genius this year and the leadership of a woman is just unbelievable.

22:55.907 --> 22:58.251
I will follow the leadership of a woman any day.

22:58.271 --> 23:01.936
So mama said, know me, well, this is who you are.

23:01.956 --> 23:04.940
So the next day she made me two burritos.

23:06.543 --> 23:07.884
And she said, here's one for you.

23:08.445 --> 23:09.867
And here's one to share with a friend.

23:16.316 --> 23:17.458
So Wednesday,

23:18.082 --> 23:19.283
was my burrito nightmare.

23:20.725 --> 23:22.947
Thursday, I shared a burrito with a friend.

23:23.969 --> 23:26.692
Friday, I was selling burritos for 25 cents a piece.

23:32.398 --> 23:38.425
As a child, that was my first revelation that was gonna create a revolution.

23:40.247 --> 23:41.428
What was that revelation?

23:42.509 --> 23:42.990
Here it is.

23:43.670 --> 23:44.892
I want you to get a hold of this.

23:45.392 --> 23:46.994
I want you to teach your children this.

23:47.458 --> 23:56.110
that revelation was this, that as much as I wanted to be like them, I was never created to fit in.

23:56.130 --> 23:59.555
I was always created to stand out.

24:00.897 --> 24:03.480
None of you in here were you ever created to fit in.

24:03.500 --> 24:05.463
You were never created to be like them.

24:05.503 --> 24:07.966
You were created to stand out.

24:08.948 --> 24:11.271
Your child is never created to fit in.

24:11.571 --> 24:13.113
That's why you could go back in your life.

24:13.173 --> 24:16.498
I've never been able to be like her like him because you're not supposed to.

24:18.018 --> 24:22.023
That revelation grew into a revolution in my life.

24:23.185 --> 24:26.449
I realized that no matter how hard I tried, I was never gonna fit in.

24:28.572 --> 24:30.214
So I quit school, I wasn't proud of that.

24:30.234 --> 24:44.394
I quit school, worked as a gardener, killed chicken for a living, had a chicken ranch, and then I worked at a car wash. We're gonna have the car wash. One of my friends pulls up and he has a Frito-Lay uniform on it.

24:44.434 --> 24:47.698
He told me that he just got hired at Frito-Lay.

24:48.578 --> 24:52.302
If they were taking an applicant, I thought, oh my God, just think if I could get a job at Frito-Lay.

24:54.004 --> 24:56.547
I could change the legacy for the Montagnets family.

24:56.567 --> 24:58.609
I can go from the fields into the factories.

25:00.050 --> 25:01.472
They have health benefits.

25:02.813 --> 25:04.956
Being Latino, I never had health benefits.

25:05.737 --> 25:07.258
You know what my health benefit was?

25:08.419 --> 25:12.204
Vicks in a seven-up.

25:12.224 --> 25:12.984
It didn't really work.

25:14.646 --> 25:18.130
So I went and applied, I couldn't read and write, so I asked the manager, can I bring it back?

25:18.530 --> 25:20.672
The application said, yeah, sure no problem.

25:20.692 --> 25:26.778
So Judy filled it out for me, went back the next day, and showed him the application.

25:27.259 --> 25:29.061
And I wasn't nervous.

25:29.081 --> 25:31.363
He looked at it, looked at me.

25:32.344 --> 25:33.165
Did you fill this out?

25:34.146 --> 25:34.626
I said, yes.

25:35.407 --> 25:36.448
You have nice handwriting.

25:38.530 --> 25:40.232
I've been still in Judy's credit ever since.

25:40.252 --> 25:43.135
1976.

25:43.335 --> 25:46.578
I got the job on the spot.

25:47.394 --> 25:54.245
Now, I thank God for a lot of things, but that day in 1976, I thank God for one thing.

25:55.086 --> 25:56.248
You know what that one thing is?

25:56.288 --> 26:00.334
They didn't do background checks in those days.

26:02.257 --> 26:03.519
I got the job on the spot.

26:04.060 --> 26:05.162
Hey, God.

26:06.624 --> 26:07.746
I got the job as a janitor.

26:09.148 --> 26:11.792
Went home to the labor camp to tell my grandpa and my dad.

26:11.812 --> 26:15.378
My grandpa told me something, ladies and gentlemen, that I believe it's the reason I'm successful today.

26:16.482 --> 26:18.744
I love my compensation, but it was never about that.

26:19.225 --> 26:20.966
I love PepsiCo, but it was never about them.

26:21.327 --> 26:23.028
I love hot cheese, but it was never about that.

26:23.989 --> 26:24.990
My grandpa said, what are you doing?

26:25.030 --> 26:25.691
I'm on my floor.

26:25.871 --> 26:28.093
He said, when you mount that floor, you make sure that it shines.

26:28.133 --> 26:30.575
And when people see it, they know that I'm Montagnier's motto.

26:30.595 --> 26:32.197
You know that I took that on, ladies and gentlemen.

26:32.237 --> 26:33.158
I shined that floor.

26:35.360 --> 26:36.521
And everybody was asking.

26:38.003 --> 26:41.306
You see, there's an old incorrect quote.

26:42.106 --> 26:43.668
You get promoted by who you know.

26:44.389 --> 26:44.949
Throw that away.

26:45.009 --> 26:45.810
That's not true.

26:47.138 --> 26:48.880
You get promoted by who knows you.

26:50.943 --> 27:00.336
You could say you know the CEO all you want, but if they don't know you, let me put it this way.

27:01.959 --> 27:09.689
You can say you know Jesus Christ all you want, but if you don't know you, so I took that on.

27:10.511 --> 27:13.615
And then I realized, you know what ladies and gentlemen, the whole world's trying to influence the world.

27:13.715 --> 27:15.858
I'm not trying to influence everyone.

27:17.506 --> 27:19.870
I'm not trying to influence everyone, only the right ones.

27:21.012 --> 27:23.456
Because when it's the right ones, it works for both of us.

27:23.657 --> 27:24.979
You help me and I help you.

27:31.370 --> 27:34.255
So that one thing that's in your hand, God will use.

27:35.277 --> 27:36.780
So one day we go grocery shopping.

27:37.541 --> 27:39.044
It's either Friday, Saturday and Sunday.

27:39.745 --> 27:42.610
And I'd go to the neighborhood market, it was called Ranch Market.

27:42.882 --> 27:44.845
And I would go there because the owner knew who I was.

27:44.885 --> 27:45.846
He would cash my check.

27:45.907 --> 27:46.848
I didn't have a bank account.

27:46.868 --> 27:48.090
Somebody said, why don't you have a bank account?

27:48.110 --> 27:48.731
I didn't have no money.

27:48.751 --> 27:50.173
What do I have a bank account for?

27:51.775 --> 27:52.697
But he would cash my check.

27:52.717 --> 27:53.438
I'd buy groceries.

27:54.319 --> 27:56.943
You know that today I teach the banking industry across the country.

27:58.686 --> 28:01.069
Today I teach the banking industry across the country.

28:03.393 --> 28:06.117
I got kicked out of a bank one time because I've bounced so many checks.

28:07.739 --> 28:08.781
That's just experience.

28:10.463 --> 28:11.465
Nothing bad about that.

28:11.705 --> 28:12.466
I survived it.

28:18.050 --> 28:19.392
So I'm not trying to influence everyone.

28:20.914 --> 28:24.898
Only the right ones.

28:24.918 --> 28:26.260
So we're grocery shopping.

28:26.280 --> 28:27.161
We walk outside.

28:27.702 --> 28:29.464
There was this young man that was always there.

28:30.585 --> 28:32.768
And he would be selling corn on the cobby lotas.

28:33.890 --> 28:36.653
And he was a food vendor before it was popular.

28:37.033 --> 28:38.275
Over 30 years ago.

28:38.996 --> 28:40.998
And he was there with two little girls and his wife.

28:41.038 --> 28:43.902
And he had a nice chest, cup of rice chest, and a table.

28:44.363 --> 28:45.544
And he'd have hot water in there.

28:45.564 --> 28:47.186
And he'd have the corn in there.

28:47.426 --> 28:48.907
And he was always dressed really nice.

28:50.048 --> 28:53.592
Now, he never acted like a food vendor.

28:53.612 --> 28:54.433
You know what he acted like?

28:55.914 --> 28:57.676
Like he was running a five-star restaurant.

28:59.317 --> 29:00.538
He greeted me with a smile.

29:01.019 --> 29:02.440
Hello, Richard, how are you?

29:02.460 --> 29:03.161
How's everybody?

29:03.741 --> 29:04.602
Just inspiring.

29:04.622 --> 29:08.166
You know, it's kind of people that just, you know, light up the room.

29:08.466 --> 29:09.086
He was one of them.

29:09.907 --> 29:12.249
And I said, well, let me have two, one for me and my oldest son.

29:14.271 --> 29:16.133
With everything, you know, they put chili on it.

29:16.233 --> 29:17.074
They put, you know,

29:17.378 --> 29:18.520
You see them at the fairs, right?

29:20.523 --> 29:22.165
They don't have to, control it with everything.

29:22.185 --> 29:22.907
Yeah, put everything on it.

29:23.087 --> 29:23.848
Chilly, yeah, yeah.

29:25.250 --> 29:26.913
And remember, we sat down on our porch.

29:26.933 --> 29:30.198
We had the old concrete porches sat during me and my son.

29:32.762 --> 29:34.304
God can use whatever's in your hand.

29:35.747 --> 29:36.788
And remember, I took a bite.

29:38.371 --> 29:38.912
I looked at her.

29:39.793 --> 29:43.058
God was about to give me a revolution.

29:44.066 --> 29:47.051
A revelation that would give me the biggest revolution of my life.

29:47.211 --> 29:50.897
I looked at it, I took a bite, took a second bite, and I said this.

29:52.019 --> 29:53.901
Every great leader has got to say these words.

29:56.466 --> 29:57.507
That looks like a cheetah.

29:59.951 --> 30:05.700
I said this, what if I put chili on a cheetah?

30:07.383 --> 30:12.050
So I ran inside and I told Judy, hey, I'm gonna put your chili sauce

30:13.538 --> 30:14.219
on Cheetos.

30:15.341 --> 30:18.746
And, you know, she's from the hood too, so she's gained like, well, let's do it.

30:20.008 --> 30:23.773
You know, so she said, go to the plant, pick up some Cheetos with no cheese on it.

30:24.675 --> 30:30.303
So I remember I got me a trash bag, and I went to the Cheetah line without any cheese, and I filled up that trash bag.

30:30.744 --> 30:31.425
I put that try.

30:31.445 --> 30:32.626
I told you I was ghetto.

30:34.169 --> 30:37.373
I always tell people when they say, man, you're still ghetto, yeah, but I'm ghetto rich.

30:40.398 --> 30:43.122
So after a couple of days, we got it fine.

30:43.362 --> 30:44.383
She took some of her work.

30:44.423 --> 30:45.484
I took some to my work.

30:46.005 --> 30:47.467
And we both came back that evening.

30:47.487 --> 30:49.169
She said, Richard, you got to call the CEO.

30:50.831 --> 30:52.512
God used that one thing that was in my hand.

30:54.054 --> 30:54.695
Call the CEO.

30:54.715 --> 30:56.037
I'm not calling the CEO.

30:56.617 --> 30:59.200
This is during when corporate America was a command in control.

30:59.220 --> 31:00.221
What is a command in control?

31:00.281 --> 31:01.042
Exactly that.

31:02.043 --> 31:03.385
I didn't hire you to think.

31:03.405 --> 31:05.227
I hired you to do what I'd tell you to do.

31:05.327 --> 31:06.328
Command and control.

31:08.671 --> 31:09.552
Just call the CEO.

31:09.572 --> 31:10.313
I'm not conscious.

31:10.333 --> 31:11.314
Okay, I'll call him.

31:11.618 --> 31:13.982
The next day I went in, and there's no email.

31:15.284 --> 31:21.714
You know, it's either a fax or a telephone, but every company had a corporate directory.

31:21.734 --> 31:22.756
I say, do today.

31:23.357 --> 31:29.427
And I found the CEO, and the first one was, you know, his name, I called him up.

31:30.469 --> 31:36.418
And keep in mind that only the presidents of the different divisions would call the CEO.

31:36.999 --> 31:38.802
A vice president would even call the CEO.

31:41.378 --> 31:45.102
So Patty, his executive assistant, answered the phone.

31:45.122 --> 31:48.305
And remember, I'm not trying to influence everyone, only the right ones.

31:48.325 --> 31:49.246
She was one of the right ones.

31:50.147 --> 31:53.350
Because I said, hi, can I speak to the CEO?

31:53.430 --> 31:54.091
She goes, who is this?

31:54.211 --> 31:54.932
Richard Montagnier?

31:54.952 --> 31:56.053
Because I don't recognize the name.

31:57.094 --> 32:00.778
Because she's used to a president from the north to south, whatever.

32:01.879 --> 32:03.841
And I said, I work in California.

32:04.302 --> 32:05.703
Oh, you're the president of California?

32:05.743 --> 32:08.466
No, I work in Southern California.

32:09.282 --> 32:12.127
Oh, you're the Vice President, no, I work in the plan.

32:12.187 --> 32:13.829
Okay, you're the Vice President of Operation.

32:13.849 --> 32:15.292
No, I work inside, inside.

32:17.656 --> 32:19.799
Plan director, no, plan manager, what are you?

32:20.721 --> 32:23.685
I got a little fancy, I said, I'm a maintenance technician.

32:25.428 --> 32:27.912
And I said, but please don't hang up, don't hang up.

32:29.275 --> 32:35.024
I saw Mr. Enrico's video and he said he act like an owner and I created my own seasoning for a new product.

32:35.064 --> 32:36.306
I think it'll save jobs.

32:37.282 --> 32:41.186
And I told her, and by the way, I was employee of the month, two months in a row.

32:43.608 --> 32:44.008
I was.

32:45.770 --> 32:47.051
And she said, hang on.

32:49.774 --> 32:54.458
She influenced him the way an executive assistant can.

32:55.579 --> 33:00.824
She told him, you need to get on the phone and talk to this gentleman.

33:01.324 --> 33:02.626
He saw your video.

33:02.846 --> 33:04.848
He's doing exactly what you said to do.

33:05.128 --> 33:07.250
And he created, you need to get on that phone.

33:08.226 --> 33:11.470
Not trying to influence everyone, only the right ones.

33:13.754 --> 33:17.238
So when he got on the phone, he was so excited, Richard, I heard you got an idea, and I'm like, yeah, yeah, yeah.

33:17.519 --> 33:19.982
I got this, you know, because I'll be there in two weeks.

33:20.443 --> 33:22.686
He's coming to, man, I was floating.

33:23.707 --> 33:25.189
But remember this command and control.

33:26.111 --> 33:27.453
Protocol goes into action.

33:28.474 --> 33:37.266
The CEO's office calls, the president's office calls, the senior vice president calls, the area vice president calls, the division vice president, the plant manager, the conversation was all the same.

33:38.882 --> 33:40.564
Who let the janitor call the CEO?

33:43.428 --> 33:44.389
Who's this Richard guy?

33:45.590 --> 33:47.693
So by the time the plan manager got it, guess what?

33:47.713 --> 33:49.836
He came looking for me and he just let me have it.

33:51.818 --> 33:54.602
The way they talk to you in the 70s, ask your parents.

33:56.244 --> 34:00.389
And he looked at me and he said, you're doing a presentation.

34:01.771 --> 34:02.892
I'm doing a presentation.

34:03.273 --> 34:04.434
I've never even done homework.

34:06.050 --> 34:09.635
So I remember I went home and Judy looked at me and she knew something around, because guess what?

34:09.695 --> 34:13.000
The plan was, let Richard do it so that he can get fired.

34:13.340 --> 34:16.104
They can see this nonsense and let's stop this now.

34:16.725 --> 34:17.867
Before it goes any further.

34:20.471 --> 34:21.993
So she looked at me and she goes, what's wrong?

34:23.194 --> 34:24.316
I said, I'm gonna get fired.

34:25.758 --> 34:27.200
And she said, why are you gonna get fired?

34:28.562 --> 34:31.346
Because you told me to call the CEO and now I'm in trouble.

34:34.274 --> 34:35.676
Typical leadership of a woman.

34:35.716 --> 34:36.477
Here's what she said.

34:37.098 --> 34:37.639
Calm down.

34:38.239 --> 34:41.604
We're gonna go to the library and check out a book on how to develop a marketing strategy.

34:43.206 --> 34:46.551
Went to the library, got three books, copied it.

34:47.772 --> 34:48.413
Here they come.

34:49.435 --> 34:50.997
All of them.

34:51.017 --> 34:54.662
It was historic because in those days CEOs didn't go to plants.

34:55.803 --> 35:00.269
They went to Wall Street, they went to whatever meetings, but this time they came to a plant and he brought everybody.

35:00.730 --> 35:03.794
Every chief, chief of HR, chief of marketing,

35:03.874 --> 35:05.676
Everybody was there and they were all mad.

35:05.696 --> 35:09.080
I couldn't understand why you mad at me and I had scientists.

35:09.100 --> 35:13.826
We have 300 scientists and the head scientist walked up to me and says, who do you think you are?

35:14.567 --> 35:15.168
We all can't.

35:15.308 --> 35:17.590
You see how many come down here to hear you.

35:17.610 --> 35:19.152
What are you going to offer?

35:19.212 --> 35:20.654
Don't you know that I have a PhD?

35:20.714 --> 35:21.295
I'm a doctor.

35:21.335 --> 35:24.599
I said, I got a PhD too.

35:25.600 --> 35:27.282
I'm poor, hungry and determined.

35:33.122 --> 35:35.285
Ladies and gentlemen, the Holy Spirit hit that place.

35:35.325 --> 35:40.691
Let me just tell you in 60 seconds, the Holy Spirit hit that place in my favor.

35:41.632 --> 35:48.982
Because the knowledge that I brought separated me from the knowledge of the most educated people in my organization, there was no competition.

35:50.503 --> 35:51.985
It didn't matter what I said.

35:52.005 --> 35:55.289
They were gonna hear what God wants them to hear.

35:55.309 --> 35:59.534
I've learned that when I come into a match, it doesn't matter what I say.

35:59.635 --> 36:02.418
God's gonna let you hear what you need to hear.

36:06.146 --> 36:08.129
So Hot Cheaters came into existence.

36:08.169 --> 36:11.495
Today was the number one snack in the world, $2 billion a year.

36:12.757 --> 36:18.205
After that, I created 14 other products that do 500 to $1 billion a year.

36:19.647 --> 36:27.079
And it just left me on a journey that I cannot explain, but it was one revelation that created a revolution.

36:29.002 --> 36:33.810
